---
import '@fontsource-variable/cinzel';
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

// ------------------------------------------------------------------
// THE DECK. Each card is one object — add a new mental model by
// adding an entry here. No other code changes needed.
// title: lines of the front word. back: paragraphs (own words).
// ------------------------------------------------------------------
const cards = [
  {
    num: '№ 001',
    title: ['ANTI', 'FRAGILE'],
    subtitle: 'Beyond resilience — what gains from disorder.',
    back: [
      'Some things break under stress. Some merely endure it. A rare third kind improves from it — gaining strength from shocks, volatility, and disorder.',
      'The resilient resists a blow and stays the same; the antifragile is remade stronger by it — muscle under load, immunity after exposure, a system that needs a little chaos to stay alive.',
    ],
    attrib: 'after Nassim Taleb, Antifragile (2012)',
  },
  {
    num: '№ 002',
    title: ['BARBELL', 'STRATEGY'],
    subtitle: 'Extreme safety plus small extreme risk — never the middle.',
    back: [
      'Put most of what you have where almost nothing can hurt it, and a small remainder where the upside is unlimited. Avoid the deceptive middle ground that is neither safe nor rewarding.',
      'The shape caps your worst case while leaving your best case open — you can only lose the small side, but you can win with it enormously.',
    ],
    attrib: 'after Nassim Taleb, Antifragile (2012)',
  },
  {
    num: '№ 003',
    title: ['VIA', 'NEGATIVA'],
    subtitle: 'Improve by removing, not by adding.',
    back: [
      'Knowledge of what is wrong is more durable than knowledge of what is right. So subtract first: remove the harmful, the fragile, the unnecessary — before reaching for anything new.',
      'Health by removing the toxin, clarity by cutting the clutter, strength by deleting the weakness. The absence of a negative often beats the presence of a positive.',
    ],
    attrib: 'after Nassim Taleb & classical theology',
  },
  {
    num: '№ 004',
    title: ['REFLEX', 'IVITY'],
    subtitle: 'Belief bends the thing it is a belief about.',
    back: [
      'In some systems, perceiving the thing changes the thing. Belief moves the fundamentals, the moved fundamentals confirm the belief, and cause and effect run in a loop instead of a line — the two spiralling together until the loop snaps.',
      'A company seen as the leader draws cheaper money, better hires and more trusting customers, and so becomes the leader. Past a threshold, the story is not noise; it is load-bearing. The same loop runs just as fast in reverse.',
    ],
    attrib: 'after George Soros, The Alchemy of Finance (1987)',
  },
  {
    num: '№ 005',
    title: ['CIRCLE OF', 'COMPETENCE'],
    subtitle: 'Act inside earned knowledge; know exactly where its edge is.',
    back: [
      'Everyone has a domain where their judgment is genuinely reliable, and a larger one where it merely feels reliable. The circle is the border between them, and the skill is not widening it — it is knowing precisely where it ends.',
      'The expensive mistakes never come from what you know you do not know. They come from the ground where you think you know and do not. So ask of any belief: did I earn this, or absorb it?',
    ],
    attrib: 'after Charlie Munger & Warren Buffett',
  },
  {
    num: '№ 006',
    title: ['THE', 'INCENTIVE'],
    subtitle: "Show me the incentive and I'll show you the outcome.",
    back: [
      'Behaviour follows incentives, not intentions. To understand why a person, a company or a system does what it does, stop reading the stated goals and read the reward structure. The output matches the incentive almost every time.',
      'The uncomfortable half of the model is turning it inward. What do your own rewards actually pay you to do — and is it the thing you say you want?',
    ],
    attrib: 'after Charlie Munger, on reward superresponse',
  },
  {
    num: '№ 007',
    title: ['OPPORTUNITY', 'COST'],
    subtitle: 'The real price is the best alternative you gave up.',
    back: [
      'The cost of a choice is never what you spent. It is the best thing you did not do instead. Time and attention are finite, so every yes is a silent no to something else.',
      'Munger measures comparatively: do not weigh an opportunity against doing nothing, weigh it against the best option already on your table. If it cannot beat that, it is not an opportunity.',
    ],
    attrib: 'after Charlie Munger & Warren Buffett',
  },
  {
    num: '№ 008',
    title: ['MARGIN OF', 'SAFETY'],
    subtitle: 'Insurance for being wrong — not a prediction of being right.',
    back: [
      'An engineer expecting ten-thousand-pound trucks rates the bridge for thirty thousand. Not pessimism about the trucks — honesty about her own measurements. Leave that same gap between what you pay and what you believe it is worth.',
      'The margin is sized to how wrong your estimate could be, never to how confident you feel. Confidence is precisely the thing it is insuring against.',
    ],
    attrib: 'after Benjamin Graham; kept by Munger & Buffett',
  },
  {
    num: '№ 009',
    title: ['LOLLA', 'PALOOZA'],
    subtitle: 'When several forces push one way, outcomes multiply.',
    back: [
      'When two, three, four forces all push in the same direction, you do not get a bigger result — you get a non-linear one. The effects multiply instead of adding. Unbreakable moats, sudden crashes and unshakeable habits are all built this way.',
      'Read it both ways. As a warning: how many biases are pushing me toward this at once? As a design: stop over-tuning one factor and stack several that point the same way.',
    ],
    attrib: 'after Charlie Munger, Elementary Worldly Wisdom (1994)',
  },
  {
    num: '№ 010',
    title: ['FIRST', 'PRINCIPLES'],
    subtitle: 'Reason up from bedrock, not across from precedent.',
    back: [
      'Most thinking is reasoning by analogy: it worked for them, so a modified version should work for me. Fast, cheap, and right most of the time — but it can only ever produce variations on what already exists.',
      'The alternative is to break the problem down to the few things you know are true, the facts that cannot be reduced further, and rebuild upward from there. It is expensive, so spend it where the stakes are high and the standard answer is old.',
    ],
    attrib: 'after Aristotle; sharpened by Elon Musk',
  },
];
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Holographic model cards"
  description="A deck of mental models as holographic cards. Browse with the arrows, watch light cross the letterforms, click a card to flip it for the definition."
>
  <p class="folio crumb"><a href="/tinkering/">Tinkering</a> · experiment 001</p>
  <h1>Holographic model cards</h1>
  <p class="lede">
    A deck of mental models. Browse with the arrows, move your cursor for the
    light, click the center card to flip it.
  </p>

  <p class="center folio keys-legend">
    <span class="keycap">←</span> <span class="keycap">→</span> cards
    <span class="sep">·</span>
    <span class="keycap">↑</span> <span class="keycap">↓</span> flip
  </p>

  <div class="stage" id="stage">
    <div class="track" id="track">
      {cards.map((c, i) => (
        <div
          class={`flip${i === 0 ? ' active' : ''}`}
          data-index={i}
          data-share={c.title.join(' ')}
          style={`--len:${Math.max(...c.title.map((line) => line.length))}`}
        >
          <div class="flip-inner">
            <div class="face front">
              <div class="front-head">
                <span class="folio">Mental model</span>
                <span class="folio">{c.num}</span>
              </div>
              <!-- SLOT: sketchnote — replace the inner placeholder with your inline SVG artwork -->
              <div class="sketch-slot" aria-hidden="true">
                <span class="folio">sketchnote here</span>
              </div>
              <div class="front-main">
                <!-- SLOT: title — replace .word with your inline SVG lettering when ready -->
                <span class="word" aria-hidden="true">{c.title[0]}<br />{c.title[1]}</span>
                <p class="subtitle">{c.subtitle}<br />A mental model.</p>
              </div>
              <span class="flip-hint folio">click to flip ↻</span>
            </div>
            <div class="face back">
              <span class="corner folio tl">{c.title.join('')}</span>
              <div class="back-body">
                {c.back.map((p) => <p>{p}</p>)}
                <p class="attrib folio">— {c.attrib}</p>
              </div>
              <span class="corner folio br">↻ flip back</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>

    <button class="nav prev" id="prev" aria-label="Previous card">‹</button>
    <button class="nav next" id="next" aria-label="Next card">›</button>
  </div>

  <p class="center folio counter"><span id="counter">1</span> / {cards.length}</p>

  <div class="share" aria-label="Share this deck">
    <span class="folio share-label">Share</span>
    <button class="share-btn folio" data-net="x" type="button">X</button>
    <button class="share-btn folio" data-net="facebook" type="button">Facebook</button>
    <button class="share-btn folio" data-net="linkedin" type="button">LinkedIn</button>
    <button class="share-btn folio" data-net="copy" type="button" id="copy-btn">Copy link</button>
    <button class="share-btn folio" data-net="native" type="button" id="native-share" hidden>More…</button>
  </div>

  <p class="center">
    <button id="motion-btn" class="motion" hidden>Enable tilt (motion sensor)</button>
  </p>

  <div class="prose">
    <h2>How it works</h2>
    <p>
      The cards are data, not markup — each mental model is an entry in a list,
      and the page renders the whole deck from it. The carousel is a single row
      shifted with a transform; the center card is live (pointer-driven light,
      click to flip), the neighbors wait faded at the sides. Arrow keys work too.
    </p>
    <p>
      Honest notes: on iPhone, motion sensors need a permission tap. With
      reduced motion switched on, slides and flips become instant cuts. Keyboard:
      ← → browse the deck, ↑ ↓ flip the card you're on.
    </p>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  /* one central axis for the whole page */
  .crumb { text-align: center; max-width: none; }
  h1 { text-align: center; }
  .lede {
    font-size: var(--step-1); color: var(--ink-muted);
    text-align: center; max-width: 44ch; margin-inline: auto;
  }
  .center { text-align: center; max-width: none; margin-inline: auto; }
  .counter { margin-top: 0.5rem; letter-spacing: 0.2em; }

  .stage {
    position: relative;
    overflow: hidden;
    padding: 3.5rem 0;
    touch-action: manipulation;
    /* full-bleed: break out of the main column to the viewport edges */
    width: 100vw;
    margin-inline: calc(50% - 50vw);
  }
  /* the breakout can add a few px of horizontal overflow from the
     scrollbar; clip it at the page level */
  :global(body) { overflow-x: clip; }

  .track {
    display: flex;
    gap: 2.25rem;
    transition: transform 0.55s cubic-bezier(0.25, 0.8, 0.3, 1);
    will-change: transform;
  }

  .flip {
    --rx: 0deg; --ry: 0deg; --mx: -60%; --my: -60%;
    flex: 0 0 auto;
    width: min(400px, 78vw);
    aspect-ratio: 5 / 7;
    transform: perspective(900px) rotateX(var(--rx)) rotateY(var(--ry));
    perspective: 1100px;
    scale: 0.82;
    transition: transform 0.09s ease-out, scale 0.45s ease, opacity 0.45s ease, filter 0.45s ease;
    opacity: 0.3;
    filter: saturate(0.6);
    cursor: pointer;
    will-change: transform;
  }
  .flip.active {
    scale: 1;
    opacity: 1;
    filter: none;
  }

  .flip-inner {
    position: relative; width: 100%; height: 100%;
    transform-style: preserve-3d;
    transition: transform 0.7s cubic-bezier(0.2, 0.7, 0.2, 1);
  }
  .flip.flipped-up .flip-inner { transform: rotateX(180deg); }
  .flip.flipped-down .flip-inner { transform: rotateX(-180deg); }

  .face {
    position: absolute; inset: 0;
    backface-visibility: hidden; -webkit-backface-visibility: hidden;
    border-radius: 12px; overflow: hidden;
    background: radial-gradient(140% 110% at 30% 8%, #191c25 0%, #14161d 55%, #101218 100%);
    box-shadow: 0 24px 60px rgba(8, 10, 16, 0.5), inset 0 0 0 1px rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.05);
    display: grid; place-content: center; padding: 2rem;
  }
  .face::before {
    content: ''; position: absolute; inset: 0 0 auto 0; height: 1px;
    background: linear-gradient(90deg, transparent 8%, rgba(255,255,255,0.28) 50%, transparent 92%);
    pointer-events: none;
  }
  /* dim ambient sheen on the front surface — the room light grazing
     the lacquer, not the white-hot glint of the letters */
  .front::after {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    background: radial-gradient(
      520px 520px at var(--mx) var(--my),
      rgba(220, 228, 248, 0.085) 0%,
      rgba(220, 228, 248, 0.035) 38%,
      transparent 70%
    );
    pointer-events: none;
  }

  .back { transform: rotateX(180deg); }
  .back::after {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    background: radial-gradient(
      520px 520px at var(--mx) calc(100% - var(--my)),
      rgba(220, 228, 248, 0.085) 0%,
      rgba(220, 228, 248, 0.035) 38%,
      transparent 70%
    );
    pointer-events: none;
  }

  .front {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    padding: 1.4rem 1.5rem 2.5rem;
    /* the title sizes itself against the card, not the viewport */
    container-type: inline-size;
  }
  .front-head {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: center;
  }
  .front-head .folio { color: rgba(205, 210, 225, 0.38); }
  .sketch-slot {
    margin-top: 0.9rem;
    height: 64px;
    border: 1px dashed #4a4e5a;
    border-radius: 8px;
    display: grid;
    place-items: center;
  }
  .sketch-slot .folio { color: #6d7284; font-size: 0.64rem; }
  .front-main {
    flex: 1;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    gap: 1.2rem;
  }
  .word {
    font-family: 'Cinzel Variable', 'Trajan Pro', Georgia, serif;
    font-weight: 560;
    /* --len is the longest line's character count; 112cqi/len keeps every
       title the same optical width, so long words shrink instead of spilling */
    font-size: clamp(1.6rem, calc(112cqi / var(--len, 8)), 3.6rem);
    letter-spacing: 0.06em; line-height: 1.12; text-align: center;
    background-image:
      /* foil band: sharp streak with tinted edges — the visible shine */
      linear-gradient(105deg,
        transparent calc(var(--mx) - 24%),
        rgba(212, 228, 251, 0.55) calc(var(--mx) - 10%),
        #ffffff calc(var(--mx) - 2%),
        #ffffff calc(var(--mx) + 2%),
        rgba(243, 221, 248, 0.55) calc(var(--mx) + 10%),
        transparent calc(var(--mx) + 24%)),
      /* soft glow following the full light position */
      radial-gradient(294px 294px at var(--mx) var(--my),
        rgba(255,255,255,0.75) 0%, rgba(255,255,255,0.35) 30%,
        transparent 62%),
      /* the resting metal */
      linear-gradient(
        180deg,
        #eef1f8 0%, #8990a0 28%, #3d424f 47%,
        #2b2f3a 53%, #868d9d 74%, #dde2ec 100%
      );
    background-clip: text; -webkit-background-clip: text; color: transparent;
    user-select: none;
  }
  .subtitle {
    font-family: var(--font-body); font-size: 0.9rem; font-style: italic;
    line-height: 1.55; text-align: center; color: #8d93a8;
    margin: 0; max-width: 28ch; justify-self: center;
  }

  .back-body { max-width: 30ch; text-align: center; }
  .back .tl {
    background-image:
      linear-gradient(105deg,
        transparent calc(var(--mx) - 18%),
        rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.9) var(--mx),
        transparent calc(var(--mx) + 18%)),
      linear-gradient(rgba(205, 210, 225, 0.38), rgba(205, 210, 225, 0.38));
    background-clip: text;
    -webkit-background-clip: text;
    color: transparent;
  }
  .back-body p {
    font-family: var(--font-body); color: #c9cedd;
    font-size: 0.95rem; line-height: 1.6; margin: 0 0 0.85rem; max-width: none;
  }
  .attrib { color: #7e849a !important; font-style: normal; margin-top: 0.35rem !important; }

  .corner { position: absolute; color: rgba(205, 210, 225, 0.38); }
  .tl { top: 1rem; left: 1.2rem; }
  .br { bottom: 1rem; right: 1.2rem; }
  .flip-hint {
    position: absolute; bottom: 1rem; left: 50%; transform: translateX(-50%);
    color: rgba(205, 210, 225, 0.3); font-size: 0.62rem;
  }

  .nav {
    position: absolute; top: 50%; translate: 0 -50%;
    z-index: 2; cursor: pointer;
    width: 2.75rem; height: 2.75rem; border-radius: 50%;
    border: 1px solid var(--hairline); background: var(--paper);
    color: var(--ink); font-size: 1.4rem; line-height: 1;
    display: grid; place-items: center;
    box-shadow: 0 2px 10px rgba(20, 22, 29, 0.12);
    transition: border-color 0.25s ease, color 0.25s ease, opacity 0.25s ease;
  }
  .nav:hover { border-color: var(--foil); color: var(--foil); }
  .nav:disabled { opacity: 0.25; cursor: default; }
  .nav:disabled:hover { border-color: var(--hairline); color: var(--ink); }
  .prev { left: clamp(0.25rem, 2vw, 1.25rem); }
  .next { right: clamp(0.25rem, 2vw, 1.25rem); }

  .share {
    display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; justify-content: center; align-items: center;
    gap: 0.6rem; margin-top: 1rem;
  }
  .share-label { color: var(--ink-muted); margin-right: 0.25rem; }
  .share-btn {
    cursor: pointer; background: none;
    border: 1px solid var(--hairline); border-radius: 4px;
    padding: 0.4rem 0.85rem; color: var(--ink-muted);
    transition: border-color 0.25s ease, color 0.25s ease;
  }
  .share-btn:hover { border-color: var(--foil); color: var(--foil); }
  .keys-legend {
    margin: 0 auto 0.5rem;
    color: var(--ink-muted);
    font-size: 0.82rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    gap: 0.4rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }
  .keys-legend .keycap {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    min-width: 1.5rem;
    height: 1.5rem;
    padding: 0 0.3rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--hairline);
    border-radius: 5px;
    background: #fff;
    color: var(--ink);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    line-height: 1;
    box-shadow: 0 1px 0 var(--hairline);
  }
  .keys-legend .sep { opacity: 0.5; margin: 0 0.25rem; }

  .motion {
    cursor: pointer; font-family: var(--font-utility);
    font-size: 0.78rem; letter-spacing: 0.1em; text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--ink); background: none;
    border: 1px solid var(--ink); border-radius: 4px; padding: 0.7rem 1.3rem;
  }
  .motion:hover { border-color: var(--cloth); color: var(--cloth); }

  .prose { margin-top: 3rem; margin-inline: auto; }
  .prose h2 { text-align: center; }

  @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
    .track, .flip, .flip-inner { transition: none; }
  }
</style>

<script>
  const stage = document.getElementById('stage');
  const track = document.getElementById('track');
  const prev = document.getElementById('prev');
  const next = document.getElementById('next');
  const counter = document.getElementById('counter');
  const btn = document.getElementById('motion-btn');
  const flips = Array.from(track.querySelectorAll('.flip'));
  const reduced = window.matchMedia('(prefers-reduced-motion: reduce)').matches;
  const MAX_TILT = 12;

  let active = 0;

  // ---- carousel positioning: center the active card ----
  function layout() {
    const card = flips[active];
    const stageW = stage.clientWidth;
    const cardW = card.offsetWidth;
    const gap = parseFloat(getComputedStyle(track).gap) || 0;
    const offset = active * (cardW + gap);
    const centerShift = (stageW - cardW) / 2;
    track.style.transform = `translateX(${centerShift - offset}px)`;
  }

  function go(index) {
    active = Math.max(0, Math.min(flips.length - 1, index));
    flips.forEach((f, i) => {
      f.classList.toggle('active', i === active);
      unflip(f); // arrive at fronts, always
      resetTilt(f);
    });
    prev.disabled = active === 0;
    next.disabled = active === flips.length - 1;
    counter.textContent = active + 1;
    layout();
  }

  prev.addEventListener('click', () => go(active - 1));
  next.addEventListener('click', () => go(active + 1));
  window.addEventListener('resize', layout);
  document.addEventListener('keydown', (e) => {
    // don't hijack keys while the user is in a form control or button
    const t = e.target;
    if (t && (t.tagName === 'INPUT' || t.tagName === 'TEXTAREA' || t.tagName === 'SELECT' || t.tagName === 'BUTTON')) return;
    if (e.key === 'ArrowLeft') { e.preventDefault(); go(active - 1); }
    if (e.key === 'ArrowRight') { e.preventDefault(); go(active + 1); }
    if (e.key === 'ArrowUp') { e.preventDefault(); flipDir(flips[active], 'up'); }
    if (e.key === 'ArrowDown') { e.preventDefault(); flipDir(flips[active], 'down'); }
  });

  // side cards navigate on click (they're pointer-events:none, so
  // catch it on the track via elementFromPoint fallback: simplest is
  // enabling clicks through a delegated handler on stage)
  stage.addEventListener('click', (e) => {
    const el = e.target.closest('.flip');
    if (el && !el.classList.contains('active')) {
      go(Number(el.dataset.index));
    }
  });

  // ---- flip: only the active card; up/down are real directions ----
  function isFlipped(f) {
    return f.classList.contains('flipped-up') || f.classList.contains('flipped-down');
  }
  function unflip(f) { f.classList.remove('flipped-up', 'flipped-down'); }
  function flipDir(f, dir) {
    if (isFlipped(f)) { unflip(f); return; }
    f.classList.add(dir === 'down' ? 'flipped-down' : 'flipped-up');
  }

  flips.forEach((f) => {
    f.addEventListener('click', () => {
      if (!f.classList.contains('active')) return;
      flipDir(f, 'up');
    });
    f.setAttribute('tabindex', '0');
    f.setAttribute('role', 'button');
    f.addEventListener('keydown', (e) => {
      if ((e.key === 'Enter' || e.key === ' ') && f.classList.contains('active')) {
        e.preventDefault(); flipDir(f, 'up');
      }
    });
  });

  // ---- light + tilt on the active card ----
  function setLight(f, px, py) {
    f.style.setProperty('--ry', `${(px * 2 * MAX_TILT).toFixed(2)}deg`);
    f.style.setProperty('--rx', `${(-py * 2 * MAX_TILT).toFixed(2)}deg`);
    f.style.setProperty('--mx', `${(50 + px * 110).toFixed(1)}%`);
    f.style.setProperty('--my', `${(42 + py * 110).toFixed(1)}%`);
  }
  function resetTilt(f) {
    f.style.setProperty('--rx', '0deg');
    f.style.setProperty('--ry', '0deg');
    f.style.setProperty('--mx', '-60%'); /* park the light off-card: */
    f.style.setProperty('--my', '-60%'); /* pure metal at rest        */
  }

  if (!reduced) {
    stage.addEventListener('pointermove', (e) => {
      const f = flips[active];
      const r = f.getBoundingClientRect();
      const px = (e.clientX - r.left) / r.width - 0.5;
      const py = (e.clientY - r.top) / r.height - 0.5;
      setLight(f, Math.max(-0.5, Math.min(0.5, px)), Math.max(-0.5, Math.min(0.5, py)));
    });
    stage.addEventListener('pointerleave', () => resetTilt(flips[active]));

    const hasOrientation = 'DeviceOrientationEvent' in window;
    const needsPermission = hasOrientation &&
      typeof window.DeviceOrientationEvent.requestPermission === 'function';
    function startGyro() {
      window.addEventListener('deviceorientation', (e) => {
        const f = flips[active];
        if (e.beta == null || e.gamma == null) return;
        const px = Math.max(-0.5, Math.min(0.5, e.gamma / 60));
        const py = Math.max(-0.5, Math.min(0.5, (e.beta - 40) / 60));
        setLight(f, px, py);
      });
    }
    if (needsPermission && btn) {
      btn.hidden = false;
      btn.addEventListener('click', async (ev) => {
        ev.stopPropagation();
        try {
          const state = await window.DeviceOrientationEvent.requestPermission();
          if (state === 'granted') { startGyro(); btn.hidden = true; }
        } catch { /* declined */ }
      });
    } else if (hasOrientation) {
      startGyro();
    }
  }

  // ---- share: links built on click so they carry the ACTIVE card ----
  const nativeBtn = document.getElementById('native-share');
  if (navigator.share && nativeBtn) nativeBtn.hidden = false;

  function shareData() {
    const name = flips[active].dataset.share || 'Mental model cards';
    return {
      url: window.location.href,
      text: `${name} — a holographic mental model card`,
      title: document.title,
    };
  }

  document.querySelectorAll('.share-btn').forEach((b) => {
    b.addEventListener('click', async () => {
      const { url, text, title } = shareData();
      const eu = encodeURIComponent(url);
      const et = encodeURIComponent(text);
      const net = b.dataset.net;
      if (net === 'x') {
        window.open(`https://twitter.com/intent/tweet?text=${et}&url=${eu}`, '_blank', 'noopener');
      } else if (net === 'facebook') {
        window.open(`https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=${eu}`, '_blank', 'noopener');
      } else if (net === 'linkedin') {
        window.open(`https://www.linkedin.com/sharing/share-offsite/?url=${eu}`, '_blank', 'noopener');
      } else if (net === 'copy') {
        try {
          await navigator.clipboard.writeText(url);
          const old = b.textContent;
          b.textContent = 'Copied ✓';
          setTimeout(() => { b.textContent = old; }, 1600);
        } catch { /* clipboard blocked — no-op */ }
      } else if (net === 'native') {
        try { await navigator.share({ url, text, title }); } catch { /* cancelled */ }
      }
    });
  });

  // initial
  go(0);
</script>
